This paper is about semantic parsing, which involves understanding natural language queries and mapping them to logical forms. This is a common problem in natural language processing and falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also uses machine learning techniques, specifically a tensor product kernel, which falls under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves classification, which falls under information retrieval (cs.IR) and neural networks (cs.NE).
